      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__xsecure__lms__client__apis_1ga018eb7459ba7c57482b7721a3026f4ef" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XSecure_LmsSignVerify</definition>
        <argsstring>(XSecure_ClientInstance *InstancePtr, const XSecure_LmsParams *ParamsPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XSecure_LmsSignVerify</name>
        <param>
          <type>XSecure_ClientInstance *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_x_secure___lms_params" kindref="compound">XSecure_LmsParams</ref> *</type>
          <declname>ParamsPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends an IPI request to perform an LMS signature verification operation. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The data, signature and public-key buffers must be reachable by the server (i.e. placed in shared memory or DDR that the PLM can access) and their addresses / lengths must already be populated in the params structure. The caller is responsible for keeping ParamsPtr (and the buffers it references) alive and coherent until this call returns.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the client instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to a populated <ref refid="struct_x_secure___lms_params" kindref="compound">XSecure_LmsParams</ref> structure.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS On successful signature verification.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_INVALID_PARAM If any input pointer is NULL.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE If the verification or transport fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
